explanation:
The report is correct. In the compiled form when _DEBUG is defined the code yields

  if (1) { ... }
  else mhd_assert(...);

The 'if (1)' is a constant-true conditional so the attached else branch is statically unreachable. MISRA C:2023 Rule 2.1 forbids unreachable code in the project, so this construct (under the _DEBUG build) violates Rule 2.1. Note that when _DEBUG is not defined the else is removed by the preprocessor and no unreachable code remains in that configuration — the violation occurs for the build configuration that defines _DEBUG.
